            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It was indeed a bug fixed in https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/git/git.git/commit/?id=8c3713cede71e4741dac546f787734627329f55b commit, included in the 2.26.0 release.\r\nHowever, `git stash push --message` works across Git versions 2.13..2.26, so isn't that better solution here, considerig that the patch is as trivial as checking the Git version? I don't think the `git stash` short-alias would change second time.",
