            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> It was indeed a bug fixed in https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/git/git.git/commit/?id=8c3713cede71e4741dac546f787734627329f55b commit, included in the 2.26.0 release.\r\n\r\nThat's a nice detective work. Thanks!\r\n\r\n> However, `git stash push --message` works across Git versions 2.13..2.26, so isn't that better solution here, considerig that the patch is as trivial as checking the Git version? I don't think the `git stash` short-alias would change second time.\r\n\r\nYeah, looks okay. Could you please make the explanatory comment either a bit more concise or format with a smaller width (ideally 80). I know that 100 is set as a maximum line length, but I don't think that does (or should) apply to comments.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAlso just in case. @ArtAndreev, could you please check this PR's code to see if this fixes an issue for you?",
